Haze Node - Public Testnet Build ({{TAG}})
===========================================

THIS IS TESTNET. NOT MAINNET. HAZE HAS NO VALUE.
The chain may still be reset (wiped back to block 0) if a serious bug is
found. Nothing you do here - balances, stakes, names, minted assets - is
guaranteed to survive. Do not treat any HAZE balance as real or valuable.


RUNNING THE NODE
-----------------
From a terminal, in the folder you extracted this archive into:

    Windows:        haze.exe node --peers wss://haze-b3l9.onrender.com/v1/p2p/ws
    macOS / Linux:  ./haze node --peers wss://haze-b3l9.onrender.com/v1/p2p/ws

This starts a node listening for peer connections on 127.0.0.1:8333 and
serving a local HTTP API on 127.0.0.1:8332. See "CONNECTING TO OTHER PEERS"
below for the current seed node address - without --peers, your node starts
its own standalone chain from genesis instead of joining the public testnet.

Useful flags:
    --rpc-port <port>     change the local HTTP API port (default 8332)
    --bind <addr:port>    change the P2P listen address (default 127.0.0.1:8333)
    --peers <addr,addr>   comma-separated list of peer addresses to connect to
    --stake-key <key>     see "ABOUT VALIDATOR STAKING" below

Run `haze --help` (or `haze node --help`) for the full list.


WHERE YOUR DATA IS STORED
--------------------------
The node stores its chain database under the HAZE_DATA_DIR environment
variable if set, otherwise in a `haze_data` folder created next to wherever
you run the binary from. Deleting this folder resets your local node back
to genesis - it does not affect anyone else's node.


CHECKING SYNC STATUS
----------------------
While the node is running, in another terminal:

    curl http://127.0.0.1:8332/v1/status

This returns your node's current chain height, tip hash, number of active
validators, and mempool size. If you connected to the public testnet via
--peers, this height should climb toward the network's current tip as your
node syncs.


CONNECTING TO OTHER PEERS
---------------------------
Public testnet seed node: wss://haze-b3l9.onrender.com/v1/p2p/ws - pass
this via --peers to join the live network instead of starting your own
standalone chain. This is a WebSocket address, not a plain addr:port -
the seed node runs behind Render, which only proxies one HTTPS port, so
P2P traffic rides over a WebSocket on that same port rather than the
usual raw TCP (this binary's --peers accepts both wss://... and plain
addr:port peers, and will keep working the same way if the seed node's
address changes later - check https://github.com/Pranav00x/haze for the
current one if this one stops responding).


ABOUT VALIDATOR STAKING
--------------------------
Registering a UTXO as a validator stake (via the `stake` wallet command)
does not mean your node will propose blocks. It submits a signed proof of
ownership - never your output's raw private key - which only takes effect
once a proposer mines it into a block; your node isn't an active validator
until then. To actually propose blocks with a staked output, you separately
need to run a node with `--stake-key <that output's private key>` -
registering and proposing are two different steps.


VERIFYING YOUR DOWNLOAD
--------------------------
Each release archive ships with a matching .sha256 file. To verify:

    macOS / Linux:  shasum -a 256 -c haze-testnet-*.tar.gz.sha256
    Windows:        certutil -hashfile haze-testnet-*.zip SHA256
                    (compare the output against the .sha256 file by hand)


